RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 80. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 24 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Louisiana Bred NW2 $5000 & NW3 $5000 Not Considered In Eligi bility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PI YO PRINCESS was just off the pace early, matched strides with the leader after the half mile pole, was set down for the drive after the quarter pole and out lasted the competition. GURKHA GOLD (IRE) sent for the rail early and set the pace, was pressured by another rival by the half, matched strides through the turn and down the lane but gave way late. TEXAS TIDELANDS settled a few lengths off the leaders early, traveled in company with a another competitor down the backside, this set moved up behind the leaders going into the turn, made a move at the quarter pole but just missed. CAVIAR RESOLUTION traveled in a set from the three path behind the leaders, flattened out at the quarter pole. HONORARY GUEST chased the leaders early and never really got involved.

ENTRY.NAME: Honorary Guest
ENTRY.OWNER: Poetsch, Hans and Roussel III, Louie J.
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased and never got involved.

ENTRY.NAME: Texas Tidelands
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, hooked company 2W, closed late, not enough

ENTRY.NAME: Pi Yo Princess
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, matched strides, out lasted

ENTRY.NAME: Caviar Resolution
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, hooked another competitor 3W, chased, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Gurkha Gold (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: rail trip, set pace, battled down the lane, came up short

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 50000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000 In Their Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GO BROTHER GO settled three deep, made a sweeping move through the second turn, came to level terms once straightened for the drive. was kept to task and kicked away through the final furlong. TRADER PRICE was nearest the pace off of the inside, bid between rivals leaving the second turn, continued on willingly but was unable to go on with the winner late. IRON N STEEL opened clear to dictate terms, was collared leaving the second turn, gave in but stayed on to preserve the minor award. OUR HEATSEEKER attended the pace toward the inside, shifted out to make a mild bid between foes going into the second turn, but failed to sustain the drive. DOUBLE ON THE RED was allowed to settle near the inside, angled out but lacked a response when called upon. RUN ON ACES was unhurried into stride, tucked in to save ground, but was never a factor. RENATI went wide, came up empty before going six furlongs, dropped well back and was distanced through the stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Our Heatseeker
ENTRY.OWNER: Hernandez Earl J Hernandez Keith J and Duvieilh John
ENTRY.COMMENT: attended pace inside, shifted out, mild bid, failed to sustain

ENTRY.NAME: Iron N Steel
ENTRY.COMMENT: opened clear, set pace, collared leaving 2nd turn, gave in

ENTRY.NAME: Double On the Red
ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, angled out into lane, failed to make headway

ENTRY.NAME: Trader Price
ENTRY.COMMENT: nearest pace, off rail, bid between, unable to go on with winner

ENTRY.NAME: Go Brother Go
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled 3w, sweeping move 4w, drew even upper, edged clear

ENTRY.NAME: Renati
ENTRY.COMMENT: wide, empty before going 3/4, dropped out

ENTRY.NAME: Run On Aces
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, tucked in, lacked a response

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR THREE YEAR OLDS. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since January 24 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOUNT KENYA was allowed to settle from the three path early in the race was moved up to join the second tier of horses around the half mile marker, was in contention from the outside at the quarter pole, battled in three way battle for half of the stretch, then battled with one other foe down to the wire and got the head nod. MOTOWN MISSILE set the early pace from the rail, was challenged in the second turn by two other foes, dug in for the drive, shook one of the challengers at the eighth pole, kept on battling with an outside foe was game but lost the nod today. SEEKING SPLENDOR settled off the pace early, moved up at the half mile pole, challenged for the lead at the quarter pole and stopped. IZEONDEC was off a step slow, had a rail trip but was never involved. MAJOR DEAL got in tight going into the first turn, bounced of the rail and showed little after that. MASQUERADE BALL was three wide through the first turn, gained ground on the leader and hooked company by the five eighths, was in between horses at the half and faltered. KING TUFF was in tight in the first turn, clipped heels with another foe and went wrong.

ENTRY.COMMENT: in tight, bounced of rail 1st turn, showed little

ENTRY.NAME: King Tuff
ENTRY.COMMENT: clipped heals first turn, went wrong, vanned off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAMMER JAMMER set the pressured pace along the inside, shook clear entering the stretch and widened. ACTION SEEKER tracked the leaders along the inside, moved into striking distance leaving the turn, angled out and took dead aim entering the stretch, but was unable to bridge the gap. CAT FIVE settled saving ground, took closer order on the turn, shifted out into the lane and churned on to earn the minor award. G'S LAW was unhurried along the inside, got through and improved position. FASTNFURIOUS disputed the pace outside the winner, weakened after a half, drifted out some into the stretch and gave way. LET'S GO RANDOM stalked three wide, moved up four wide to make a mild bid, was fanned wider still leaving the turn and faded. UNAFFILIATED was through early. HE IS WORTHY broke slow and was always outrun.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Special Weight Purse 50000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $30,000 In Their Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANDERS SMILE was sent out for the lead, showed the way from the rail and got to the wire first. CAJUN CONNECTION bobbled at the start ,settled a few lengths off the leaders early, was in contention in the turn, ran flat. PESO PESADO trailed early from the outside, moved up just off the leader at the half, was five wide was within striking distance at the quarter pole but never fired. SYVESTAR was off the pace early, stayed along the rail was accompanied by two other competitors at the half, where he lugged out pushing the horse next to him into the horse on the far out side causing the to loose their strides continued to race along the rail down the lane where he finished flat. IRON MOON was wide early, moved up into contention around the half mile marker, was jostled around by another foe, raced further on while still wide and retreated after the quarter pole. HARPES HILL vied for the lead early, settled for second tier in the first turn on the outside, shuffled back, where he was 2W, moved in contention at the half mile marker in between horses, was bumped by a foe on the inside, was eased in the lane and walked off. AFTER A STEWART'S INQUIRY INVOVING SYVESTAR, HARPERS HILL AND IRON MOON, THE STEWART FOUND THAT SYVESTAR INERFERRED WITH BOTH HARPERS HILL AND IRON MOON AND WAS DISQSUALIFIED AND PLACED SIXTH.

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Syvestar
ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace rail trip, lugged out around the half, chased.

ENTRY.NAME: Harpes Hill
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4W 1st turn,shuffledback,2nd tier1/2, jostled, eased

ENTRY.NAME: Anders Smile
ENTRY.COMMENT: sent, set pace, prevailed

ENTRY.NAME: Cajun Connection
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled at the start off pace, 2nd tier, closed

ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed out start, 5W, moved up 1/2, never fired.

ENTRY.COMMENT: outside 6W first turn, jostled at the 1/2, retreated

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR GROUNDS RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 80. Allowance Purse 51000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 24 Allowed 3 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $20,000 Or Less N ot Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COPTER attended the pace along the inside, shifted out leaving the turn, forged command four wide, dug in and maintained a diminishing advantage. LORDY LORDY was hustled along between foes, came five wide, kicked on well but was unable to reach the winner. HOOSIER was slow into stride, swung to the outside entering the stretch, finished well and was making up ground with every stride. CLEAR AS A BELE broke a step slow, tucked in to save ground, ranged into contention through the turn, was stymied in traffic a quarter out, got through between rivals and continued on willingly. CALICOCO was allowed to settle, advanced between foes into the lane, but failed to make serious headway. SONO came away in good order, was allowed to settle while wide, weakened leaving the turn and faded. BLINDEDBYTHEGEES contested the pace along the inside, disputed the issue to the final furlong and succumbed. GEAUX SUGAR vied for the lead outside, was collared between horses entering the stretch and gave way readily.

FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, WAIVER CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 117 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over On The Turf Since January 24 Allowed 3 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $15,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $25,000 In Their Last 3 Starts). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this rac e over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and 70 Yards.) (Rail at 34 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PERRINS was unhurried into stride, tucked in to save ground, came under a ride with three furlongs to run, ranged into striking position on the second turn, split rivals entering the stretch, struck the front and quickly drew clear. ONEFORVIVI pressed the pace outside, forged command entering the stretch, kept on well but was no match for the winner. SCORING DRIVE stalked the pace toward the inside, shifted out entering the stretch, loomed a danger but lacked the needed late response. MOMENT OF STARDOM settled in hand, angled out five wide to make his bid, but failed to make headway through the drive. BOULDERING was allowed to settle, came five wide, angled inward in traffic but went evenly. NORTHERNREFLECTION contended between horses to the second turn and tired. WESTERN STAR set the pressured pace along the inside through the second turn and dropped out. OLE STUD MUFFIN went wide and was never a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: DUXONTHEPOND was allowed to settle, launched a looping move five wide, reeled in the leader and was up in the final strides.
